snippet.title: Barnaba feat Diamond Platnumz - Salama (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Music video by  Barnaba and Diamond Platnumz tells the emotional story of a man reaching out to his ex-lover, asking how she’s doing now that she’s moved on. The lyrics reveal a mix of reflection and subtle confrontation, as he acknowledges that she seems to be thriving in a new relationship filled with peace, joy, and genuine love—something they lacked in the past. The song carries an undertone of regret and unresolved emotions, while also calling out the ex for once treating him as if he wasn’t good enough. Now, having found someone who truly values him, he indirectly questions her past judgments. It’s a soulful, melodic piece that explores themes of growth, healing, and the bittersweet nature of moving on. This song marks Barnaba’s Celebrations of 16 years in his role as a performing artist while still having a lot to achieve he remains focused to achieve a lot and climb heights of excellency on his music journey, while you listen to this track be inspired of greatness and enjoy the best sounds from the best. snippet.title: Kenya police fire tear gas at protesters in Nairobi over blogger’s death in custody
snippet.description:
Police in Kenya's capital Nairobi have fired tear gas at protesters angered by the death of a 31-year-old blogger in police custody. 
President William Ruto earlier said the man died “at the hands of the police”, contradicting initial accounts of his death. 
Officials had claimed he died due to self-inflicted injuries, but an autopsy revealed that he was assaulted. 
The blogger was known for being critical about political and social issues. 

Al Jazeera’s Malcolm Webb is covering the protests from the front line in Nairobi, Kenya.

snippet.title: Mid-East Crisis escalates - Iran rains missiles on Israel after attacks on nuclear sites | BBC News
snippet.description:
Iran has launched mass new strikes on Israel.  It says it attacked dozens of targets including military centres and airbases.   Smoke has been seen rising over the skyscrapers of Tel Aviv and there have been explosions in Jerusalem.  

The  bombardment is in retaliation for Israel's strikes on Iran, hitting military and nuclear sites.   It says it hit a nuclear facility in Isfahan following earlier strikes on the country's biggest nuclear facility at Natanz .Israel said the attacks were vital to prevent Iran developing a nuclear weapon.  

Iran’s spiritual leader, Ayatollah Khamenei, promised his country would 'inflict heavy blows' in response.
 
There are warnings the conflict could escalate into all-out war.

snippet.title: "Police Killed Him": Ruto Breaks Silence on Activist Ojwang's Death | Firstpost Africa | N18G
snippet.description:
"Police Killed Him": Ruto Breaks Silence on Activist Ojwang's Death | Firstpost Africa | N18G

Kenya’s President William Ruto has publicly condemned the death of 31-year-old Albert Ojwang, who died in police custody after being arrested over a social media post accusing a top police officer of corruption. Police initially claimed Ojwang died by hitting his head against a wall, but a government pathologist later said his injuries were unlikely to be self-inflicted. Ruto called the death “heartbreaking and unacceptable” and urged a swift investigation. The case has sparked outrage across Kenya, which is still reeling from last year’s deadly anti-government protests. Five police officers have been suspended, and international voices, including the U.S. and UK, are demanding justice. Rights groups say this reflects a larger pattern of police abuse and silencing of critics.
